The paper deals with encoding and decoding algorithms for quantization of vectors, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) categories. The use of random operators and least squares minimization also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Additionally, the exponential decay in approximation error implies a numerical analysis (cs.NA) component.
